..I kill XD Today was my first day of school, I was as tired as hell so I drank a full glass of coffee for breakfast. I think that made me sick, and I felt terrible throughout the day. I felt like I was going to fall over in my classes.... anyways. What a wonderful day today was. I hope I sleep tonight. and that I wont feel sick tommorow... all my teachers seem nice enough. In english we had to interview all of the class members. I got interviewed and was forced to be social. I think I scared them by my answers :D.. Them: Favorite color? Me: Bloody panda... -_- Them: O_O; what? Me: Bloody panda -_- Them: *scribble on paper* ._. Them: Do you have any children? Me: *annoyed*... I ate them >:O Them: ..ok... *walks away* ... That was the highlight of my day, watching their face expressions as I answered those pointless questions. My psychology teacher seems great, it looks like a class i'll enjoy except for the "socializing" part of it. We have a lot of group projects and crap like that. I preffer to work alone. Art is calming, theres only one other person with me in the airbrush room. So i'll get a lot done in that class, since i'll be bored out of my mind. Accounting, simple enough... meh I dont have my own computer though since the classes are so crowded. Web site development, that teacher makes me laugh. I had her my sophomore year... she wants to see my art O_O;. Civics/ american goverment... another teacher ive already had before. Seems like a regular boring history class... yeah.

I have a new cd player..I named him  +--+ Hora +--+. That is all, Im going to go whine about sleep now. Bai... and i'll go online tommorow, I promise. Even if it's for only a second. I also have a new picture I'll post up on deviantart tommorow.

brought to you by Quizilla ... I dont sleep though.. *shrugs* ..I went to my uncles house today, it was fairly boring at first.. nothing to do. But then later on we went to the mall of orange?..I didnt even know they had one. Anyways..I got a Tare panda notebook, now I can write more evil things that I make up in my mind. Meh, stupid people hitting on me. There was this old asian guy, with pretty Ryutarou hair. Who kept on staring at me... scary. But I walked by him and he nodded while flashing me a big smile, I smiled back because I thought his hair was pretty, im such a dork... it looked all shiny and soft! I wanted to pet it. Anyways.. we went back to their home...and I was bored again.. I did get to go to the comic store and I got petshop of horrors volume two. I love that manga. I made more icons, but im greedy and selfish so I decided to keep them to myself. Even if I have no more space on my lj for them. I want to go to Japan now... I cant wait until next July. <lj user=" clockworklunacy"> are we doing anything tommorow?

For some reason, lately I just feel, blah...I dont feel like doing anything it used to be laziness but now it's turned into something unrecognizable. Anyways.. I took random pictures today, since there was nothing else better to do, my brother took some odd ones too. Tommorow I get to go to my uncles house, oh im drowning in my joy. There is nothing to do over there but sit and listen to other people talk. If im lucky i'll convince my mom to take me to that comic book store, ive been wanting to get petshop of horrors volume two. Actually, I really want to go to kino and get a jrock magazine, that would be nice... but I doubt i'll be able to go anytime soon. Earlier today my mom and I were looking at jrock pictures, it's good that she can tolerate it now. I even showed her the Obscure pv clip up at Dir en Grey's site. She thought it was "Intresting"... I have yet to show her that Meevs picture/ flyer I came across today. I wonder if I'll sleep, I miss sleep... I miss closing my eyes to drift off into unconsciousness... but now thats what terrifies me. ... im so stupid... *erases post*


........


 I think i'll be going now, if I ever do plan to fall asleep...I know if I stay on longer the hours will pass me by..and next thing i'll notice is the sun shining through the window... Good-night.
